Dani Alves has defended his Barcelona reputation by insisting he has created more goals for Lionel Messi than any other player.

Alves has come under fire for the perceived inaccuracy of his crossing in recent weeks, but insists he is still the master creator.

The Brazil full back is out of contract at the end of this season and although Barcelona have opened negotiations with Messi's chief supplier, his future at the club is far from certain.

