Alves, 31, has been with the Catalan club since 2008, and says it is a 'personal challenge' to stay with the club.

'I've survived because I know the expectations that there always are here. I always set myself challenges and staying at Barca is a personal challenge of mine.

'I want to leave with a feeling that my time at Barça has been awesome. I never think in the long term. So in the short term I want to see out my current contract here'. 

